# Monorepo architecture

Three layers — respect boundaries:

1. **`packages/ui`** — Gluestack v5 design system (NativeWind v5 + Tailwind CSS v4). Components + theme only. No screens, auth, Convex, or Solito.
2. **`packages/app`** — screens, auth, db client. Composes `@app-template/ui`.
3. **`apps/web` + `apps/mobile`** — thin routes and platform wiring only.

When adding UI:
- Reusable presentational piece → `packages/ui`
- Full screen or feature logic → `packages/app/src/screens`
- Route file → one-line re-export in `apps/web` or `apps/mobile`

Convex backend lives in repo-root `convex/`. Never duplicate backend logic in apps.

Shared screens use React Native components (rendered on web via react-native-web). Navigation in shared code uses Solito.
